metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #109
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Paper City Dreams #18
metadata.description:
A city made of paper,
crafted with care,
using RoughJS and Hashure Gap
to build buildings with flair.

Rectangles stacked on top of each other,
cast shadows on the ground,
a cross-hash adding depth
to the structures all around.

A city of lines and shapes,
a city of texture and hue,
a generative art masterpiece

metadata.name: 365 Tentacles #30
metadata.description:
Wow, Fxhash ! What a year !

For #fxhashturnsone I decided to explore how far I could take a simple concept: drawing 365 tentacles.
This turned out to be an interesting exercise, as having a strict limitation seemed to spark more ideas than when having complete freedom. There's a lot you can do with 365 things !

99.9% of primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Key commands:
's' to save a png image
'1', '2', '4' to change resolution
'+', '-' to change rendering zoom

metadata.name: Play with lines #zentangle #7
metadata.description:
Once upon a time, there was a sect called the Dotted and the Lined
They considered the point and line sacred!
And they believed that the world started with a point and moved with a line
And the points made the world!


Play with lines
This collection is the result of my playing with the lines I drew with the tablet.
And combining these lines with digital paintings in the background
This set has 7 layers
The first layer contains the background
The second layer of perlin noise lines
The third layer of the lines I have drawn with the tablet is 28 different images in the zentangle style
The fourth layer of lines
The fifth layer of forms on the collection
The sixth and seventh layers include the cover, frame, signature, etc.

metadata.name: Moon Sun Ocean #247
metadata.description:
The secret to happiness is to simplify as much as possible. The details surrounding us must be said goodbye as soon as possible. The best thing we can do is to get started early and get rid of additional complexities as soon as possible. After that, we'll be able to breathe... After that, life will begin again!
There will be many words in this interpretation, despite its simplicity.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: EPIHYPERDERPFLARDIOIDS #236
metadata.description:
EPIHYPERDERPFLARDIOIDS

after symbol 2525, 
aint gonna need to load, write no code
everything you think, do and say
is in the streams that you watch today (oh oh oh)

We find this code is very much alive. They are epi. They are hyper. They are derp. They are flardioids.

Epihyperderpflardioids is the name I have given to a large family of symmetrical loopy shapes, based on sine waves and rotations, reminiscent of the mathematical toy game "Spirograph", but also different. I studied them extensively, but don't claim to understand them fully, yet. I hope you enjoy them as much as I do.

These 365 Epihyperderpflardioids were generated for FXhash's one year anniversary.
